FBIS3-53279 "drnes009_c_94011" FBIS-NES-94-009 Document Type:Daily Report 13 Jan 1994 Egypt Eritrean Ambassador Delivers Message, Comments NC1301104794 Cairo MENA in Arabic 0947 GMT 13 Jan 94 NC1301104794 Cairo MENA Language: Arabic Article Type:BFN [Text] Cairo, 13 Jan (MENA) -- President Husni Mubarak has received a written message from Eritrean leader Isaias Afewerki on bilateral relations and the confrontation with terrorists who recently crossed Eritrea's border. Eritrean Ambassador in Cairo Muhammad 'Ali 'Amr made a statement after a meeting with President Mubarak today. He added that he informed President Mubarak of President Afewerki's desire for cooperation in various fields. He said that he also informed President Mubarak, in his capacity as head of the largest country in the region and as chairman of the OAU, of Eritrea's wish to ward off the dangers it is facing from extremist terrorist activities near its border that have been proven to have been launched from a certain country. Eritrea was recently the target of a terrorist operation.
